// {2} sorcery: "draw a card. Delve." Pins the exile arm of the per-pip
// alternative-payment hook (PayPips): delve lets a generic pip be paid by
// exiling a card from your graveyard ([CR#702.66a]) — "rather than pay that
// mana", without lowering the {2} mana value ([CR#202.3,702.51b]). Treasure
// Cruise (the canon delve card) draws three for {7}{U}; this minimal {2}
// twin isolates the exile pip hook for a small, deterministic engine test.
// Per plugins/testing/README.md, the canon card carries the real keyword.
//
// The delve static is spelled DIRECTLY as a `PayPips` row so the engine test
// does not depend on the keyword layer.
Normal(
    name: "Sorcery Delve Draw",
    mana_cost: [Generic(2)],
    types: [Sorcery],
    abilities: [
        Spell(effect: Draw(1)),
        Static(effects: [
            PayPips(Generic, ExileToPay(AllOf([InZone(Graveyard), Owner(Ref(You))]))),
        ]),
    ],
)
